						               													<description>Pit-Witz is an abstract strategy game system made in Singapore. The rules that come with the set describe 9 games that may be played with the set.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the basic game of Pit-Witz, each player has 8 pieces and tries to get them from his corner to the opposite corner. The board is like a cross-word grid and pieces move like chess rooks. In making a move, the pieces have to move all the way down a corridor, until they encounter a dark square or another piece. Other games add the use of dice and money (called witzers).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The names of the other games are:&amp;#10;Jet-Witz&amp;#10;Banditz&amp;#10;Dice-Witz&amp;#10;Plus-Witz&amp;#10;Haggle-Witz&amp;#10;Stomp-Witz (also known as Beetles)&amp;#10;Claim-Witz&amp;#10;Morlocks&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
